*Steps to create module for testing:*

*1. Create new module*
{code}
appc new -n test --id com.appc.module.test3
### when prompted for the project type, select "Titanium Module" 
{code}

*2. Replace source and library files*

Extract [^com.module.test3.zip] and replace with module contents under *windows* diretory

*3. Compile module and install into module directory*

{code}
> cd YOUR_MODULE_PROJECT_DIR/windows
> appc ti build -p windows --build-only --run-cmake
{code}

And then install module zip in your Titanium SDK modules directory

*4. Create Titanium app project*

{code:title=app.js}
var sap = require('com.appc.module.test3');

var win = Ti.UI.createWindow({
    backgroundColor: 'green',
    layout:'vertical'
});

win.addEventListener('open', function() {
	alert(sap.testLogonCore());
});

win.open();
{code}

This should prompt "V4"

{quote}
Does this mean that, references to those .winmd will also be added to the App's Project File and TitaniumWindows_Native Project file?
{quote}

[~cesar.cavazos] Yes. Module's winmd will be also added to the app's project.
